The paper deals with image classification using Convolutional Neural Networks (CNNs), which is a popular topic in computer vision (cs.CV). The use of deep learning techniques for material classification is also a growing area of research in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also involves the evaluation of different CNN architectures, which falls under multimedia (cs.MM) and information retrieval (cs.IR) categories.
